  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equations.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}\n=\n\\hbar(1+\\chi_{\\mathrm{TZP}}).\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Delta x\\,\\Delta p\n\\geq\n\\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2}.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Delta t\\,\\Delta E\n\\geq\n\\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2}.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $\\chi_{\\mathrm{TZP}}$ encode the zero-point correction to the operational quantum scale.  \nDefine:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}\n=\n\\hbar(1+\\chi_{\\mathrm{TZP}}).\n\\end{equation}\n\nReplacing $\\hbar$ by $\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}$ in the uncertainty relations gives:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Delta x\\,\\Delta p\n\\geq\n\\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2},\n\\qquad\n\\Delta t\\,\\Delta E\n\\geq\n\\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2}.\n\\end{equation}\n\nThus no observation protocol can resolve below the effective uncertainty window:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\Omega_{\\mathrm{obs}}\n=\n\\left\\{\n(\\Delta x,\\Delta p,\\Delta t,\\Delta E):\n\\Delta x\\Delta p\\geq \\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2},\n\\;\n\\Delta t\\Delta E\\geq \\frac{\\hbar_{\\mathrm{eff}}}{2}\n\\right\\}.\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nObservability is bounded by a TZP-corrected effective quantum constant.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
